                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.753,
                                "byte_start": 89901,
                                "byte_stop": 136921,
                                "text": "I have the announcement in two cases this morning the first is number 05-1541, EC Term of Years Trust versus United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 11.753,
                                "stop": 16.67,
                                "byte_start": 136921,
                                "byte_stop": 156670,
                                "text": "Justice Souter has authored the opinion in this case, and he has asked me to announce it for him."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 16.67,
                                "stop": 22.774,
                                "byte_start": 156670,
                                "byte_stop": 181016,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.774,
                                "stop": 39.986,
                                "byte_start": 181016,
                                "byte_stop": 249875,
                                "text": "The internal revenue service determined that Elmer and Dorothy Cullers claimed unwarranted income tax deductions in the 1980s but by the time the government tried to collect from the Cullers\u2019 they have transferred some of their assets to petitioner EC Term of Years Trust."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.986,
                                "stop": 45.453,
                                "byte_start": 249875,
                                "byte_stop": 271818,
                                "text": "The IRS levied on the Trust\u2019s bank account and collected over $3 million."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.453,
                                "stop": 54.862,
                                "byte_start": 271818,
                                "byte_stop": 309434,
                                "text": "Almost a year after that the Trust filed an action claiming that the IRS has wrongfully levied on it\u2019s property to collect taxes owed by another."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.862,
                                "stop": 68.653,
                                "byte_start": 309434,
                                "byte_stop": 364605,
                                "text": "Such wrongful levy actions are specifically authorized by statute, but they are subject to a nine month filing deadline because the Trust had missed that deadline the District Court dismissed it\u2019s complain."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 68.653,
                                "stop": 82.735,
                                "byte_start": 364605,
                                "byte_stop": 420925,
                                "text": "The Trust then re-filed its action as a claim for a tax refund which has a less demanding filing deadline, but the District Court dismissed it again reasoning that a wrongful levy claim was the Trust\u2019s only recourse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.735,
                                "stop": 89.538,
                                "byte_start": 420925,
                                "byte_stop": 448092,
                                "text": "The Fifth Circuit affirmed and we granted certiorari to resolve a conflict with the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.538,
                                "stop": 93.484,
                                "byte_start": 448092,
                                "byte_stop": 463870,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed today with the Clerk of the Court, we affirm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.484,
                                "stop": 101.577,
                                "byte_start": 463870,
                                "byte_stop": 496262,
                                "text": "We have repeatedly held that when Congress creates a precisely drawn and detailed statute it preempts more general remedies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.577,
                                "stop": 109.543,
                                "byte_start": 496262,
                                "byte_stop": 528131,
                                "text": "Here Congress specifically tailored a remedy for third parties challenging a wrongful levy and provided a nine month statute of limitations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 109.543,
                                "stop": 117.775,
                                "byte_start": 528131,
                                "byte_stop": 561045,
                                "text": "That short period was no accident since the IRS must be promptly be told if it has seized property from the wrong party."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.775,
                                "stop": 132.334,
                                "byte_start": 561045,
                                "byte_stop": 619246,
                                "text": "But this deadline could be easily awaited if as the Trust argues third parties could always reformulate their wrongful levy claim as one for a tax refund, resort to a tax refund claim is therefore preempted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 132.334,
                                "stop": 142.741,
                                "byte_start": 619246,
                                "byte_stop": 660938,
                                "text": "The trust also relies on United States against Williams, a case in which we held that a wrongful lien claim could be brought in the form of a tax refund action."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.741,
                                "stop": 151.077,
                                "byte_start": 660938,
                                "byte_stop": 694270,
                                "text": "But we said in Williams that no remedy other than a tax refund was open to the plaintiff in that case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.077,
                                "stop": 160.857,
                                "byte_start": 694270,
                                "byte_stop": 733349,
                                "text": "Here on the other hand, the Trust challenges a levy not a lien and could have made a timely wrongful levy claim for the relief it now seeks."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.857,
                                "stop": 164.963,
                                "byte_start": 733349,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Souter\u2019s opinion for the Court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
